%S A258082 240,29790,24024
%N A258082 Smallest magic constant of most-perfect magic squares of order 2n composed of distinct prime numbers.
%C A258082 A magic square of order 2n is most-perfect if the following two conditions hold: (i) every 2 x 2 subsquare (including wrap-around) sum to 2T; and (ii) any pair of elements at distance n along a diagonal or a skew diagonal sum to T, where T= S/n, S is the magic constant.
%C A258082 All most-perfect magic squares are pandiagonal.
%C A258082 All pandiagonal magic squares of order 4 are most-perfect (cf. A191533).
%H A258082 N. Makarova, <a href="http://www.primepuzzles.net/puzzles/puzz_671.htm">Puzzle 671: Most Perfect Magic Squares</a>, Prime Puzzles & Problems.
